elements.contents: Sector Performance Snapshot: Banking, Finance, and IT Lead Gains Amid Mixed Market Sentiment

elements.title: undefined (MarketsMojo – Stock Market News)
elements.contents: The Indian equity market displayed a broadly positive tone on 5 December 2025, with 27 sectors advancing against 9 declining, resulting in a sector advance-decline ratio of 3.0. The BSE 500 index recorded a one-day return of 0.39%, reflecting cautious optimism among investors. Notably, the NIFTYPSUBANK, NIFTYFINANCE, and NIFTYIT sectors emerged as the top gainers, buoyed by strong performances from key stocks such as SBI, Cholaman Investment & Finance, and HCL Technologies. Conversely, sectors like NIFTYMEDIA, BSE Capital Goods, and S&P Industrials faced downward pressure, influenced by significant declines in select heavyweight stocks.

elements.contents: Jagatjit Industries Q2 FY26: Mounting Losses and Deteriorating Operations Signal Deep Distress

elements.title: undefined (MarketsMojo – Result Analysis)
elements.contents: Jagatjit Industries Ltd., the Kapurthala-based beverages manufacturer, reported a catastrophic second quarter for FY2026, with consolidated net losses ballooning to ₹27.91 crores—a staggering 249.75% deterioration year-on-year. The micro-cap company, valued at ₹789.00 crores, saw its stock trading at ₹165.00 as of December 5, down 34.78% over the past year and significantly underperforming the Sensex. The results reveal a company in acute operational distress, with negative operating margins, collapsing revenues, and mounting interest burdens that raise serious questions about financial viability.
